-- Policy document: DB/F-14 (Info) — No explicit AUTO_INCREMENT seed values in migrations
--
-- POLICY: Future migration files must NOT include explicit AUTO_INCREMENT = N seed values.
-- Production record counts must not be embedded in source-controlled migration files.
-- AUTO_INCREMENT seeds leak approximate record counts from production environments into
-- version history accessible to all repository contributors, violating information-
-- disclosure hygiene. V001 was generated by MySQL Workbench and included seed values;
-- it cannot be changed retroactively without invalidating the Flyway checksum. All
-- migrations from V002 onward must omit AUTO_INCREMENT seed assignments.
-- This migration is a no-op policy document.
SELECT 1;
